The article discusses an executive order issued by President Joe Biden to promote economy and efficiency in Federal procurement by ensuring that contractors and subcontractors who work with the Federal Government provide adequate COVID-19 safeguards for their workforce. The order requires that contracts and contract-like instruments include a clause specifying that contractors and subcontractors must comply with workplace safety guidance published by the Safer Federal Workforce Task Force. The Task Force will provide definitions, protocols, and exceptions related to COVID-19 safety for contractors and subcontractors. The order also outlines the implementation steps for agencies and the Federal Acquisition Regulatory Council. It clarifies the applicability of the order to different types of contracts and exempts certain cases. The order is effective immediately for new contracts and contract-like instruments entered into on or after October 15, 2021. It encourages agencies to ensure safety protocols for existing contracts and contract-like instruments. The order also includes general provisions regarding the authority of executive departments and agencies and the implementation of the order.